Business Brief -- Pyramid Technology Corp.:
   Operating Loss Is Expected
   For Firm's Second Quarter
The company said it will provide details when it reports
its second-quarter earnings April 22.
   Pyramid had a loss in its first quarter of $18.5 million,
or $1.56 a share, including charges of $17.7 million for
restructuring and $900,000 for settlement of litigation.
   Richard H. Lussier, chairman, president and chief
executive officer, said the company expects to begin
realizing benefits from its recent restructuring by its third
quarter. But Mr. Lussier said the company still hasn't seen
any recovery in the computer industry.